    <h3><b style="color:yellow">Stage</b></h3>
    <p style="color: white">A stage is a major step in a tournament. Its purpose is to arrange and organize the competition for some of the participants following a specific and standardized method. The method is defined by the type of stage.

        There are currently ten different types of stage supported on Toornament: single elimination, double elimination, gauntlet, round-robin groups, bracket groups, league and swiss system. And also three Free-for-all ones: simple, single elimination and bracket groups.
        
        Each has its own method to arrange matches between participants. Depending on its type, a stage may involve sub-elements of the structure: groups, rounds, matches, brackets and rankings.</p>
